%N A388456 Triangle read by rows: coefficient [t^k] of the Ehrhart polynomial of the n-dimensional cross-polytope, multiplied by n!.
%C A388456 The n-dimensional cross-polytope consists of all points (x_1,...,x_n) such that |x_1| + ... + |x_n| <= 1. The Ehrhart polynomial evaluated at t counts the number of integer lattice points in the cross-polytope dilated by a factor of t.
%C A388456 T(n,k) is also the number of permutations of size n+1 with k+1 cycles such that the cycles not containing the entry n+1 are odd, and colored red or blue. In particular, T(n,k) is nonnegative.
%H A388456 K. Menon and E. Verkama, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2512.08669">Interpreting the Ehrhart coefficients of cross-polytopes</a>, arXiv:2512.08669 [math.CO], 2025.
%F A388456 T(n,k) = Sum_{i=0..n} C(n,i)*Sum_{j=0..n-i} A132393(n-i+1,j+1)*A008275(i,k-j).
%F A388456 T(n,k) = A137394(n+2,k+2)/(n+1).
%F A388456 G.f. Sum_{t>=0,k>=0} T(n,k)*t^k*x^t = n!*(1+x)^n/((1-x)^(n+1)).
%e A388456 Triangle of T(n,k) for n<=6:
