%e A388456 The Ehrhart polynomial of the 3-dimensional cross-polytope is 1 + (8/3)t + 2t^2 + (4/3)t^3. Multiplied by 3!: 6 + 16t + 12t^2 + 8t^3. Hence, the n=3 row of the triangle is 6, 16, 12, 8.
%e A388456 Let n=3 and k=2. There are three permutations of size 4 with 3 cycles, such that all cycles not containing the entry 4 are odd: (2)(3)(1 4), (1)(3)(2 4) and (1)(2)(3 4). For each of these there are four ways of coloring the cycles not containing the entry 4, so T(3,2)=12.
%o A388456 (SageMath)
%o A388456 def T(n, k):
%o A388456   return sum(binomial(n,i)*sum(stirling_number1(n-i+1,j+1)*(-1)^(i+k+j)*stirling_number1(i,k-j) for j in range(n-i+1)) for i in range(n+1))
